                            <comment id="115789" author="stella" created="Tue, 19 May 2015 05:51:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, All:&lt;br/&gt;
The kernel version is 2.6.9-22. &lt;br/&gt;
I installed e2fsprogs-1.35-12.24.el4.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                e2fsprogs-devel-1.35-12.24.el4.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                kernel-smp-2.6.9-22.0.2.EL_lustre.1.4.6.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                kernel-source-2.6-22.0.2.EL_lustre.1.4.6.x86_64.rpm.&lt;br/&gt;
                lustre-1.4.6-2.6.9_22.0.2.EL.lustre1.4.6smp.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                lustre-debuginfo-1.4.6-2.6.9_22.0.2.EL_lustre.1.4.6smp.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                lustre-modules-1.4.6-2.6.9_22.0.2.EL_lustre.1.4.6smp.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
                lustre-source-1.4.6-2.6.9_22.0.2.EL_lustre.1.4.6smp.x86_64.rpm&lt;br/&gt;
Now, the mount.lustre command can use it&lt;br/&gt;
but when I type mount.lustre 12.12.12.1@o2ib:/lustre /mnt/client&lt;br/&gt;
The error message shows directory to mount not in nid:/mds/profile format&lt;br/&gt;
I have added options lnet ip2nets=&quot;o2ib(ib0) 12.12.12.127&quot; in modprobe.conf&lt;br/&gt;
So how do I solve this problem?       &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115504" author="adilger" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 17:14:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also note that Lustre 1.6 clients are only interoperable with Lustre 1.6 and 1.8 (and 1.4) servers, but cannot work with Lustre 2.x servers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115503" author="pjones" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 17:10:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Red Hat 4 has not been supported for Lustre for a number  of years. You will need to find a version 1.6.x or earlier to find this support.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
